sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K346089
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 promoter(BBa_I719005)+MerT+MerP+MerC(the facilitation module of mercury absorption)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part conbined MerT, MerP and MerC together under the regulation of T7 promoter. MerT,merP and merC can act together to transport Hg(II) into the cyutosol to activate promoters which are dependent on intracellular Hg(II).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: miao jing

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K346086
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is constructed for the expression of merT, which is a transmembrane protein in E.coli and can transport Hg(II) into the cytosol. MerT is also a member of the Mer operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: miao jing

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K346087
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is constructed for the expression of merP, which can bind Hg(II) in the periplasm and deliver it to merT for the transmembrane transportation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: miao jing

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K346088
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is constructed for the expression of merC. MerC can transport Hg(II) into the cytosol without the help of merP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: miao jing
